reviewText: I've loved the Carry On movies for decades and have one of the collections available in the U.S.  This one doesn't cut the mustard, though.  Too, too stupid.
Title: Carry on Christmas

reviewText: Quite outdated and the humour is a bit too coarse.  Not as funny as it was back in the time the movie was made.
Title: Carry on Christmas

reviewText: The "Carry On" gang was unique and never before or after has British comedy been quite the same, although it is up there with Laurel & Hard, Abbot & Costello and Martin & Lewis in North America and of course Charlie Chaplain, born a Brit who came to the U.S.A.!
summary: Greetings & Salutations! Thankfully more material is available on the "Carry On" comedy films and television specials!
Title: Carry on Christmas

reviewText: This DVD contains all four Christmas specials and one hour of an interview with the producer.For those of you who do not know about the carry on series, these programs are pretty racy with double meaning statements that involve British slang.  It is not suitable for young children.
Title: Carry on Christmas

reviewText: I enjoy the British sitcoms on television - did not like this movie at allto me it was truly a waste of time viewing it and a total waste of moneyin purchasing it.
Title: Carry on Christmas

reviewText: I cant remember them on TV but the 1969 one is the best, one is in black and white but all are good.
summary: If you love Carry On you'll love this set of DVDs
Title: Carry on Christmas

reviewText: Funny and not offensive like today's crap produced by Hollywood. British people have the best sense of humour !! Lots of double entendre's but harmless, good old-fashioned fun.
Title: Carry on Christmas

reviewText: This is the completion of my collection, and it's a corker. Sid James is in them (4 shows on the disc) along with some of the other regulars, and like I have said before; it is silly! But, I believe everybody should have a little silliness in there lives. I just wish the group was around today, making some more movies for us old timers to enjoy today. This is a great collection!
Title: Carry on Christmas

reviewText: As usual, this DVD lived up to the usual standard of the other carry on movies. It was worth the purchase.
Title: Carry on Christmas
